      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 represents the pinnacle of the E46 chassis, powered by the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six featuring six individual throttle bodies and double VANOS variable valve timing. The powertrain is mated to a desirable 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory limited-slip differential. Mechanical integrity is prioritized with a reinforced rear subframe and documented rod bearing service. The suspension retains its signature compliance and turn-in precision, while the hydraulic steering rack provides exceptional feedback. Finished in Titanium Silver, this example shows minor cosmetic patina consistent with its age but remains a mechanically robust, driver-spec machine with an 8,000 RPM redline.",
